events.name: New York Knicks at Atlanta Hawks

headlines.description: — Karl-Anthony Towns had 30 points and 11 rebounds, and the hot-shooting New York Knicks took command with 40 points in the second period and beat the Atlanta Hawks 121-105 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Towns scores 30 points as hot-shooting Knicks overwhelm Hawks 121-105 and await Brunson's return

headlines.description: — Desmond Bane scored 38 points, Zach Edey had a career-high 21 rebounds and the Memphis Grizzlies held off the Detroit Pistons 109-103 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Desmond Bane scores 38 in the Grizzlies' 109-103 victory over the Pistons

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards scored 37 points, Rudy Gobert added 23 points and 19 rebounds and the Minnesota Timberwolves extended their winning streak to five games with a 114-109 victory over the Philadelphia 76ers on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Edwards and Gobert power the Timberwolves to a 114-109 win over the struggling 76ers

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had 36 points, 15 rebounds and 10 assists, Kevin Porter Jr. had 24 points off the bench and the Milwaukee Bucks beat the Miami Heat 121-115 in overtime Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo's 2nd straight triple-double lifts Bucks over Heat in OT, 121-115

headlines.description: — Ivica Zubac was 11 for 11 from the floor for 25 points, Kawhi Leonard and James Harden scored 29 each and the Los Angeles Clippers blew out the Dallas Mavericks 135-104 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Zubac's perfect shooting night, Leonard and Harden lead Clippers to 135-104 blowout of Mavericks
